<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">129. Seitz, William C. The Responsive Eye. New York: Museum of Modern Art, 1965.56 pp. B/W illus., color illus. </p><p class="annot">This is the catalog for an exhibition of works from the Impressionists to Op artists. All of the works rely on human perception to achieve illusory visual effects of motion, transparency, vanishing or vibrating boundaries, and three-dimensionality. Anyone interested in special color effects will be informed by the text and inspired by the illustrations. </p></div>
